7:08 PM
There's your problem — there's no camera permission string at all in your config. Apple saw a camera request with no NSCameraUsageDescription or a default/generic one from a plugin.

Add this to your ios section in app.json:

json
"ios": {
  "supportsTablet": false,
  "bundleIdentifier": "com.alstiginc.chefscale",
  "infoPlist": {
    "NSCameraUsageDescription": "ChefScale uses your camera to scan and photograph recipes, ingredient lists, and nutrition labels so you can quickly import them into the app for scaling and cost tracking."
  }
}
That's specific, explains the purpose, and gives concrete examples — exactly what Apple wants.

Now — are you using expo-camera or expo-image-picker for the OCR scanning? If you're using expo-image-picker, you'll also need:

json
"NSPhotoLibraryUsageDescription": "ChefScale accesses your photo library so you can import photos of recipes, ingredient lists, and nutrition labels for scanning and recipe entry."
Add both to be safe. Then rebuild (bump build number to 4) and upload.

That handles Issue 3. Ready to tackle Issue 2 (the EULA/Terms link)? That one is an App Store Connect fix, no code needed.

